.TH SIMPLE_SHELL "9 July 2017" "01" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- alternate implementation of a C shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.I FORMAT
.I [ARGUMENT]
.B ...
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a simple C shell running in Linux shell in interactive and non-interactive mode.
.PP
FORMAT dictates the shell commands.
.PP
0.1 an alternative UNIX command line interpreter
.PP
0.1.1 getline - implements an alternative getline() function
.PP
0.2 handles command line with arguments
.PP
0.2.1 strtok - an alternative strtok function
.PP
0.3 PATH - handles the PATH environment variable
.PP
0.4 exit - implements the exit built-in that exits the shell
.PP
0.4.1 exit with arguments - handles arguments for the built-in exit. Format is exit status, where status is an integer used to exit the shell.
.PP
0.4.2 Ctrl+c - handles Ctrl+c by not exiting the shell
.PP
1.0 env - implements the env built-in that prints the current environment
.PP
1.1 setenv and unsetenv - implements the setenv and unsetenv builtin commands
.PP
1.2 cd - implements the built-in command, cd.
.PP
; - handles the command ";" separator
.PP
&& , || - handles the && and || logical operators
.PP
aliases - handles aliases
.PP
variable replacement - handles variable replacement, $?, and $$ variable
.PP
comments - handles # comments
.PP
help - implement the help built-in
.PP
history built-in
.PP
filename - can handle simple_shell [filename]
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Felicia Hsieh and Kiren Srinivasan
.SH REPORTING BUGS
Please report bugs to 214@holbertonschool.com and 155@holbertonschool.com
.SH SEE ALSO
shell(3xs)